{"File":"/home/lowcache/.nix-config/dots/gemini/antigravity-cli/brain/8f1e8393-afb2-49a8-aaa0-a9f8939ed4c5/.system_generated/logs/transcript_full.jsonl","LineNumber":34,"LineContent":"{\"step_index\":34,\"source\":\"MODEL\",\"type\":\"SEARCH_WEB\",\"status\":\"DONE\",\"created_at\":\"2026-06-03T12:59:31Z\",\"content\":\"Created At: 2026-06-03T12:59:31Z\\nCompleted At: 2026-06-03T12:59:36Z\\nThe search for \\\"nixos xdg-desktop-portal-gtk \\\"user-home-symbolic-ltr\\\" file chooser not opening\\\" returned the following summary:\\nThe error message regarding `user-home-symbolic-ltr` (often accompanied by a \\\"No such interface\\\" error for `org.freedesktop.portal.FileChooser`) indicates that `xdg-desktop-portal-gtk` is failing to initialize or communicate properly with your desktop environment[1][2][3].\\n\\nThis typically happens because the portal service is either not running, has crashed, or is not correctly prioritized by your XDG configuration[4][5][6].\\n\\n### Recommended Troubleshooting Steps\\n\\n#### 1. Check Service Status\\nFirst, verify if the portal service is actually running. Open your terminal and run:\\n```bash\\nsystemctl --user status xdg-desktop-portal-gtk\\n```\\nIf it is \\\"inactive,\\\" \\\"dead,\\\" or shows a failure/timeout, the service is likely failing to connect to your display or D-Bus[4][7][6].\\n\\n#### 2. Verify Your `xdg.portal` Configuration\\nEnsure your `configuration.nix` (or Home Manager config) explicitly includes the GTK portal and defines the priority for the file chooser[8][9]. A common cause is missing the `extraPortals` or failing to define which portal should handle the `FileChooser` interface[10][5][9].\\n\\nTry adding or updating this section:\\n```nix\\nxdg.portal = {\\n  enable = true;\\n  extraPortals = [ pkgs.xdg-desktop-portal-gtk ];\\n  \\n  # Ensure the GTK portal is used for file picking\\n  config = {\\n    common = {\\n      default = [ \\\"gtk\\\" ];\\n      \\\"org.freedesktop.impl.portal.FileChooser\\\" = [ \\\"gtk\\\" ];\\n    };\\n  };\\n};\\n```\\n\\n#### 3. Address Conflicts (Hyprland / Desktop Specifics)\\nIf you are using **Hyprland** or another Wayland compositor, note that `xdg-desktop-portal-hyprland` does **not** provide a file chooser[9][11]. You must have `xdg-desktop-portal-gtk` installed alongside it to \\\"fill the gaps\\\"[9][12].\\n\\nIf you recently updated your system, ensure that your `portalPackage` or `extraPortals` are not being overridden by conflicting configurations (e.g., both NixOS and Home Manager defining the same portal settings)[5][8]. Home Manager settings often take precedence over NixOS system settings[8].\\n\\n#### 4. Clear Cached Portal Configurations\\nSometimes, corrupted cache files in your home directory prevent the portal from starting[2]. You can try clearing them:\\n```bash\\nrm -rf ~/.config/xdg-desktop-portal/\\n```\\nThen, restart your session or the portal service:\\n```bash\\nsystemctl --user restart xdg-desktop-portal\\n```\\n\\n#### 5. Environment Variables\\nIf the portal is running but applications still fail, they might be missing the environment variables required to \\\"see\\\" the portal[13]. Ensure your environment is set to use the portal:\\n```nix\\nenvironment.variables = {\\n  GTK_USE_PORTAL = \\\"1\\\";\\n};\\n```\\n*Note: In some modern environments, this is handled automatically, but explicitly setting it can help debug applications that are not properly sandboxed or configured.*\\n\\n### Still failing?\\nIf you continue to see errors like `No such interface` or `startup job failed`, check your logs immediately after trying to open a file:\\n```bash\\njournalctl --user -u xdg-desktop-portal -f\\n```\\nThis will show you exactly which component is rejecting the request (e.g., a timeout or a missing D-Bus interface)[4][6].\\n\\nSources:\\n[1] [github.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGahROfk7RUXRWCqIxnG3zGiMIitzvVoatIet9cjjvxQzNllrH2EsNmTyINw85wPgznHPuWDjZru7CXWr3jHDEHj4ph50-BxcXZZoLTCnoKGNHFUh9-emx6DROGdK6RV-QDEw-CKNzhl1bcvLaweGUp8fHfnjY=)\\n[2] [nixos.org](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFhUCCcXWWWiGdmP1sxIaWZGAT-fire3HxfBMjmqSzmQGoTEunw3dKmdE6040TuaR80o9rPWGyPxqDje4Ka8iP_AWHzOTiH46N1sSbTmTjf8Q7QiLMxocVyaCGbjh3SS8SUFafKSF2oq6cZEYXXw0GY0vM1BA0kR82lfSi6fKnwXUzLCGr2eEyymks=)\\n[3] [nixos.org](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFX479uSsA5_8_mGLxv3Es0Eaiqb5CWKdsr-K_AH6yFA1tw6HeDRUY4CvBf948dEx96xiODkSeZb-zcopd-G6UFAl1feexNNM4lBH60ok-mmYQvdYwscdOr5T22dGd2FHvUFxGtpTzsZb_AwauqslkoD6qYTaws3_dEb-jGX2ZkP-x60vZst3UiSVUG)\\n[4] [archlinux.org](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEAllFv_Wvk9x_5YB5zGA5-LuPEClqbxLfbeN6dv_pzgJsLZncCDfGzoXOevuu0eeci6ce1GnlgsksJvdUmdMIVuvv8wyJsGzdLAP0YYlMai96-OZbRrNSoT-Dnth3JhC4fTA9P2EfQ)\\n[5] [reddit.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHQyDgV6YzqM_zvng41Bu4-nkYnQ_qj8qeZA3pYpjWurrvxtbymnzynuM6f40q749ozIALf1Eq3p1Iv8CidCVT3hvSFsJqubOxfSFcuPaevYunWXJN-Ht2uIrUqJ3Rb2VXyxBKP9IFWdzRFPoMOkt7QzkybRn1_V7w09nrOqnaV1Kod3a7XqKlmzD41ZR_m2MY_sHIs7NVc)\\n[6] [github.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQG9Wv6E5iIadRxlUWc3RHMzMdc3OGprZ_cSflZmNxlfpBy1j6ALFMyn7XIcfqApQ3t4IXrFDLWiMFOUOZl9g4BSiMap7EhBcB5gIm2ouoi9diSMohMXUgkcu_Eyf0SwoZOYqnKH)\\n[7] [nixos.org](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGiGBpLAa0iYO2N3KbRGb0MTZVkYEQTceV192rE3X89pkZaWkgIjIpi9RXJR4HdLih6uAiZUS5Rl5D-QrOiELWgjXYHGmD5zH7EZZsdV36_LRCgKzIFNXD1Ch6BxtBVJoe8rsFiQGiN_YdYI-p44OtYu0D-Cgmci5mN5bI=)\\n[8] [nixos.org](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGqNYsqIi9KWhgp1atIfkNhAhah-B7KUbcXgdJ8_7Ds5HBALOwRQgj0qeeVl6elFC39eIb4S1eYxHZAcMjysLKcA14Fhm__NbTBaEPGjMLO8MUnCpUsEH8JkoIv458aCtRHyqH5JXj6C3S4TBvcRV4uOxinO3hA4A==)\\n[9] [reddit.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHxjNUhflWKpBnnv30BR695M3ijA4